"yasmiṃ kho, lohicca, satthari sāvako evarūpaṃ uḷāraṃ visesaṃ adhigacchati, "
"ayampi kho, lohicca, satthā, yo loke nacodanāraho, yo ca panevarūpaṃ "
"satthāraṃ codeti, sā codanā abhūtā atacchā adhammikā sāvajjā."
msgstr ""
"A teacher under whom a disciple achieves such a high distinction is one who "
"does not deserve to be reprimanded. …"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="23"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.234"></a>
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn12:28.1"
msgid "…"
msgstr "…"

msgctxt "dn12:28.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn12:28.3"
msgid "Nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānāti."
msgstr "They understand: “… there is no return to any state of existence.”"

msgctxt "dn12:28.4"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ kho, lohicca, satthari sāvako evarūpaṃ uḷāraṃ visesaṃ adhigacchati, "
"ayampi kho, lohicca, satthā, yo loke nacodanāraho, yo ca panevarūpaṃ "
"satthāraṃ codeti, sā codanā abhūtā atacchā adhammikā sāvajjā”ti."
msgstr ""
"A teacher under whom a disciple achieves such a high distinction is one who "
"does not deserve to be reprimanded. When someone reprimands such a teacher, "
"the reprimand is false, baseless, illegitimate, and blameworthy.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="24"></a><a class="wp" id="wp78"></a>
msgctxt "dn12:29.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, lohicco brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he had spoken, Lohicca said to the Buddha:"

# At Thag 16.8, naraka is clearly a term for a cliff in a normal sense. Better to assume a naturalistic meaning here.
msgctxt "dn12:29.2"
msgid ""
"“seyyathāpi, bho gotama, puriso purisaṃ narakapapātaṃ patantaṃ kesesu "
"gahetvā uddharitvā thale patiṭṭhapeyya;"
msgstr ""
"“Suppose, Master Gotama, a person was on the verge of falling off a cliff, "
"and another person was to grab them by the hair, pull them up, and place "
"them on firm ground."

msgctxt "dn12:29.3"
msgid ""
"evamevāhaṃ bhotā gotamena narakapapātaṃ papatanto uddharitvā thale "
"patiṭṭhāpito."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when I was falling off a cliff Master Gotama pulled me up "
"and placed me on safe ground. "

msgctxt "dn12:29.4"
msgid "Abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama."
msgstr "Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent!"

msgctxt "dn12:29.5"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bho gotama, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā "
"vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya:"
msgstr ""
"As if he was righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing "
"out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark  "

msgctxt "dn12:29.6"
msgid "‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti;"
msgstr "so people with good eyes can see what’s there,  "

msgctxt "dn12:29.7"
msgid "evamevaṃ bhotā gotamena anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito."
msgstr "just so have you made the Teaching clear in many ways."

msgctxt "dn12:29.8"
msgid "Esāhaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca."
msgstr ""
"I go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the Dharma, and to the mendicant Saṅgha."

msgctxt "dn12:29.9"
msgid ""
"Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti."
msgstr ""
"From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has "
"gone for refuge for life.” "

#. </p><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "dn12:30.1"
msgid "Lohiccasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dvādasamaṃ."
msgstr ""
